# AceZone Backend

Backend service for the AceZone full-stack sports equipment shopping and rental platform.

## Overview

The backend was developed using Java Spring Boot and provides REST API endpoints for authentication, product management, shopping cart operations, favorites management, and admin functionalities.

## Features

- User authentication and authorization
- Secure login system using Spring Security
- RESTful API architecture
- Product management system
- Shopping cart functionality
- Favorites management
- Admin role with product editing permissions
- Product image upload support
- SQL database integration
- CRUD operations for products and users

## Tech Stack

- Java
- Spring Boot
- Spring Security
- REST API
- SQL Database
- Maven

## Authentication & Security

- User registration and login
- Role-based authorization
- Protected API endpoints
- Secure password handling using Spring Security

## Product Management

Admins can:
- Add new products
- Edit product information
- Delete products
- Upload product images

## Database

The application uses an SQL relational database for storing:
- Users
- Products
- Favorites
- Shopping cart data
- Orders and rentals

## API Testing

API endpoints were tested using:
- Postman


## Running the Project

```bash
mvn spring-boot:run
